## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [N542704]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Accumulates reduced amounts of starch relative to wildtype but large amounts of soluble glucan.
   - [N542704]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Modification of amylopectine structure. Strong increase of number of small chain (degree of polymerisation between 5 and 9) and decrease in number of longer chains (11-17 degree of polymerisation).
   - [N542704]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Mutants are defecting in amylopectin biosynthesis. Reduced amounts of starch and abnormal amylopectin, phytoglycogens are produced.
   - [N542704]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;No significant alteration of amylase-to-amylopectine ratio.
   - [N542704]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Reduced starch in leaves
   - [N542704]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Strong increase in water soluble polysaccharides (WSPs) content.
   - [atisa1-1 atisa2-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Accumulates reduced amounts of starch relative to wildtype but large amounts of soluble glucan.
   - [atisa1-1 atisa2-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;No reduction in maltose and matotriose production.
